</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[707,1193,194,454]" pageId="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,380,401]" pageId="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[1054,1116,379,400]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovatus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1116,379,400]" italics="true" pageId="11">ovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= eggshaped) is a Latin adjective that refers to the oval configuration of the hind body of this beetle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
